        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2734278580" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6055035580905302673">A fairly wide ranging treatise on the nature of God and theology. Not too long and makes some interesting comments here and there often responding to his contemporaries. Maimonides promotes a view that we cannot make positive claims about the attributes of God, that the universe didn&apos;t always exist, that God is the maker, the form of the world and at the same time it&apos;s purpose.</span>
  <span id="freeText6055035580905302673" style="display:none">A fairly wide ranging treatise on the nature of God and theology. Not too long and makes some interesting comments here and there often responding to his contemporaries. Maimonides promotes a view that we cannot make positive claims about the attributes of God, that the universe didn't always exist, that God is the maker, the form of the world and at the same time it's purpose.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6055035580905302673" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
