<div id="review_3261661456" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3261661456" />
    <a title="Joseph Durham" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18422734-joseph-durham"><img alt="Joseph Durham" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1363447500p2/18422734.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3261661456?book_show_action=true">Apr 03, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Joseph Durham" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Joseph Durham" href="/user/show/18422734-joseph-durham">Joseph Durham</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3261661456" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13291209282587624339">I was drawn to this book when I read about Maimonides during a Middle Ages class in college. Moses was a polymath who was able to navigate the Islamic culture of the time and yet write about his Jewish faith and became popular doing so. This is a long book, and the translator did a wonderful job of capturing the flow of his thought and expressions. In addition to his faith he wrote about astronomy, medicine, and philosophy of his time. He was born 1134 and died 1204. So this book offers a window</span>
  <span id="freeText13291209282587624339" style="display:none">I was drawn to this book when I read about Maimonides during a Middle Ages class in college. Moses was a polymath who was able to navigate the Islamic culture of the time and yet write about his Jewish faith and became popular doing so. This is a long book, and the translator did a wonderful job of capturing the flow of his thought and expressions. In addition to his faith he wrote about astronomy, medicine, and philosophy of his time. He was born 1134 and died 1204. So this book offers a window into the thought of the Middle Ages world. For such a long book with many topics is it easy to follow along. This book is an artful counterpoint to our times which has many competing voices and ideas clamoring for attention as well.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13291209282587624339" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


