<div id="review_2344584212" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2344584212" />
    <a title="Brenda Stahl" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29037553-brenda-stahl"><img alt="Brenda Stahl" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1499489697p2/29037553.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2344584212?book_show_action=true">Mar 30, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brenda Stahl" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brenda Stahl" href="/user/show/29037553-brenda-stahl">Brenda Stahl</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2344584212" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14032686352779736748">oh Moses, Moses....(maimonides).... I am still perplexed. There is some beautiful annotations within this text that refer to hebrew and linguistical arrangements - how soliloquies change based on position of the aleph or the tropal inflection. The part that left me perplexed was his inability to discern where G-d truly &quot;is,&quot; and what G-d has power/intention/love over...is it the universe? Is it our minds? Is it all encompassing?? I wish he had spent more time on breaking down omniscience and omn</span>
  <span id="freeText14032686352779736748" style="display:none">oh Moses, Moses....(maimonides).... I am still perplexed. There is some beautiful annotations within this text that refer to hebrew and linguistical arrangements - how soliloquies change based on position of the aleph or the tropal inflection. The part that left me perplexed was his inability to discern where G-d truly "is," and what G-d has power/intention/love over...is it the universe? Is it our minds? Is it all encompassing?? I wish he had spent more time on breaking down omniscience and omnipotence and omnibenevolence. A great read as we begin Pesach. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14032686352779736748" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


